17:~~~~exercism/note
18:The linked list is a fundamental data structure in computer science, often used in the implementation of other data structures.
19:As the name suggests, it is a list of nodes that are linked together.
20:It is a list of "nodes", where each node links to its neighbor or neighbors.
21:In a **singly linked list** each node links only to the node that follows it.
22:In a **doubly linked list** each node links to both the node that comes before, as well as the node that comes after.
23:
24:If you want to dig deeper into linked lists, check out [this article][intro-linked-list] that explains it using nice drawings.
